  <title>Users administration using &cockpit;</title>
  <info>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
    <para>
      The <guimenu>Accounts</guimenu> &cockpit; plugin enables you to administer user accounts.
    </para>
  </abstract>
  </info>
  <note>
   <title>Users administration only for server administrators</title>
   <para>
    Only users with the <guimenu>Server administrator</guimenu> role can edit
    other users.
   </para>
  </note>
  <para>
    Using the <guimenu>Accounts</guimenu> &cockpit; plugin, you can perform the following tasks:
  </para>  
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        creating new users of the system as described in <xref linkend="task-creating-users-cockpit"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        assigning <command>sudo</command> privileges to user accounts <xref linkend="task-modifying-user-accounts"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        forcing a change of a user's password <xref linkend="task-modifying-user-accounts"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        locking a particular user account <xref linkend="task-modifying-user-accounts"/>.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</topic>
